data.title: Piano Winners 2
data.text:
Korarit Kullarmard, a 7 years old piano player from Bangkok, Thailand, first took his piano lesson less than a year ago. It all began when he saw his 9 years old brother practise the piano every day. From that time on, he felt a strong desire to play like his brother. As for now he is actively studying at the Piano Academy of Bangkok. He has received several awards from many distinguished institutions such as WPTA Spain International Piano Competition, Vienna Music Competition, London Classical Music Competition, Orbetello Piano Competition and Golden Classical Music Award. All these years Korarit has made it clear that piano is one of his keen interests and passions and he has always been trying to practise to perfect his skill as much as possible.

Poppanut Kullarmard - a 10 years old piano enthusiast from Bangkok, Thailand has started his pianistic journey since 2017, and is actively studying at Piano Academy of Bangkok. His interest in music was well established at the age of 5 when he received a distinction score from the University of West London. Since then, he has received several awards from many distinguished institutions such as Singapore International Piano Competition, International Youth Music Competitions, Medici International Music Competition, The 1 St Bangkok International Performing Arts Piano Competition, Hong Kong Music Talent & Performance Award, Golden Classical Music Competition etc. He has also taken ABRSM Piano Performance Grade 4 and achieved the distinction score. All these years Poppanut has made it clear that piano is one of his interests and passions and he has always been trying to practice to perfect his skill as much as possible.

Isabella Nien a 2nd grader in United States, and she began studying piano in 2020 when I was 5 with Dr. Qian Yin. She enjoys performing piano and has won several award these years. In January 2022, she was selected as a First Prize winner and Best Performance Classical Composer at WPTA Spain IPC Competition, Gold Prize at Canadian International Music Competition, Silver Prize at London Young Musician Competition. In April 2022, she was selected as a 3rd place winner at Chopin Avenue Competition. In 2022 May, she was selected as Gold Prize at Quebec Music Competition. In 2022 July, she was selected as the Second Prize Winner in the Windsor International Piano Competition in UK and excited to join the winner performance at Southbank Center Purcell Hall in 2023. She was awarded the First Prize Winner at Bach International Music Competition and Third Prize at American Classical Young Musician Award Competition in 2022 September. Besides playing piano, she loves reading, swimming and classical ballet dance. She is looking forward to learning more piano pieces in many great year ahead.

Esme is 7 years old and is currently attending 1st grade at Harbor Day School in Newport Beach, CA. She has been studying the piano under the direction of Prof. Ana Maria Eckstein. She enjoys playing various composers, reading about their lives, and learning different musical eras and their musical styles. Since age 5, she has won numerous national and international music competitions including the Gold Prize in the WPTA Finland International Piano Competition 2020;First Prize + Exceptional Young Talent Special Prize Winner of the 2020 Golden Classical Music Awards International Competition; First Prize in American Protégé International Music Talent Competition 2020; First Absolute Prize + Exceptional Young Talent Special Prize Winner of the 2020 International Music Competition Bonn Grand Prize Virtuoso; First Absolute Prize + Exceptional Young Talent Special Prize Winner of the 2021 International Music Competition London Grand Prize Virtuoso. More recently, she won Gold Prize in the 2021 Golden Key Music Festival; Gold Prize in 2021 Musicale Piano Etude Festival; Gold Prize in 2021 Musicale Piano Classical music Festival; Gold Prize 2021 WPTA Finland International Piano Competition; Platinum/ Grand Champion special prize winner of 2021 Quebec Music Competition; First Prize + Exceptional Young Talent Special Prize Winner of the 2021 International Music Competition Salzburg Grand Prize Virtuoso; Gold award in all 3 categories (Junior Performance category, Bach Invention/Sinfonia Category, and Mozart category) of 2021 Nordic International Piano Competition; First Absolute Prize + Exceptional Young Talent Special Prize Winner of the 2021 Golden Classical Music Awards International Competition; First Prize in the 2021 US New Star “Etude” Competition; Gold Prize in North American Virtuoso International Music competition; Gold Award 2021 Global International Music Competition; Diamond Special Top Prize winner of Grand Maestro International Music Competition; First Prize in the 2021 US New Star International Piano Competition; Gold Prize in 2021 Musicale Fall Music Festival; American Music Judges Award for outstanding performance and interpretation at the Musicale Piano Music Festival 2021; Platinum Award in 2021 Trinity International Music Competition; Platinum/ Absolute First Prize in 2021-2022 Canadian International Music Competition; Platinum award in 2022 Euro Elite International Music Competition; Grand Prize Royal Sound Music Competition 2022; Grand Prize 21st Century Talent Music Competition 2022; First Prize Musicale winter competition;First Prize 2022 Bay Area Piano Competition; First Prize 2022 Pelican International Music Competition;First Absolute Prize + Exceptional Young Talent Special Prize at 2022 International Music Competition Salzburg and Amsterdam Platinum/ Grand Champion top prize winner of 2022 Quebec Music Competition; Most Exceptional Performer and First Prize at 2022 Charleston International Music Competition-20th century music competition; First Prize at Mimas Festival International Competition 2022; Gold Award at WPTA Finland International Piano Competition 2022; First Absolute Prize + Exceptional Young Talent Special Prize Winner of the 2021 Golden Classical Music Awards International Competition; Winner of Gold Hands award, Best 20-21st Century Performance, Best Haydn Performance, and best Bach Performance in 2022 Carles and Sofia International Piano Competition; Platinum Award 2021 Global International Music Competition; First Prize 18th century music Charleston International Music Competition 2022; First Prize winner Pacific Stars International Piano Competition 2022; Absolute Platinum Prize winner 2022 Appassionato International Youth Music Festival. She was invited to perform in various winner’s concerts since 5, including Carnegie Hall, NYC, USA ; Solitar Mozarteum, Salzburg, Vienna ; Beethoven’s House, Bonn, Germany; Royal Albert Hall, London, UK; Teatro Studio, Marco della Musica, Rome, Italy; Kleine Zaal, Concertgebouw, Amsterdam. Due to the pandemic, she was not able to travel to other concert halls except for the winner’s recital at Carnegie Hall in July 2022 but hopes one day to perform at these beautiful concert halls when travel is safer. Besides piano, Esme also enjoys reading, drawing, painting, ballet and figure skating, and playing with her brother and puppies

Jayata (Thad) Tieanworn was born in Bangkok, Thailand on 13 August 2012. He started learning piano in August 2020 when he was 8-year-old. Before being introduced to piano, Thad always engaged in many activities, such as creating Roblox and Minecraft games, ice-skating, swimming, golfing and creating his own Youtube channel. One day, we got a beautiful grand piano in our home. He was so excited and always tried to create his own song with it. Queen's "Love of My Life" was the first song that he could figure out its piano keys by himself after becoming fond of this song. Then, he continued figuring out the piano keys for other songs. So, we decide to find a piano instructor for him. He passed Grade 5 Examination of Trinity College London within 1 year after starting his very first piano lesson. He loves playing piano so much .

Phoonseeraah was born on August 14, 2008 in Bangkok, Thailand. Shewas introduced to piano at the age of 4. Examination: At the age of 13, Ada has been awarded the ATCL Associate of Trinity College London Piano, Level 4 Diploma in Music Performance. (July 2022) At the age of 11, Ada passed Grade 8 Examination in Classical Piano (with Distinction) from Trinity College London (2019) 3rd highest score on Grade 8 Piano Examination at Trinity College London (2021) Trinity Awards Thailand 2020 Winner Trophy from Trinity College London (April 2021) Concerts: Ada go the First Prize Award and will have her piano performance at the Weill Recital Hall, at Carnegie Hall in New York, USA on December 19, 2022 Ada got the Platinum Prize Award and had her piano performance at the New York Prize Winners’ Recital on August 28th, 2022 at The DiMenna Center in New York City on August 28, 2022 Ada got the Second Prize Winner Award and had her piano performance at the Weill Recital Hall, at Carnegie Hall in New York, USA on November 5, 2019 Ada got the First Prize Award and had her piano performance at the Glaserner Saal, Musikverein Concert Hall in Vienna, Austria on September 13, 2019 Ada got the Second Prize Award and has been invited to perform at the Wiener Saal, Mozarteum Concert Hall in Salzburg, Austria in July 2022. Ada got the First Prize Award and has been invited to perform at The Kleine Zaal, Concertgebouw Concert Hall in Amsterdam, the Netherlands in July 2019 Ada got the Second Prize Award and has been invited to perform at The Kleine Zaal, Concertgebouw Concert Hall in Amsterdam, the Netherlands in July 2022.

My name is Aeneas Yu and I am from north California. I am 12 years old. I started attending percussion group lessons when I was 2 years old and have been studying piano with Peyhwan Kuan since 2017. I won top prizes at USOMC, USIMC, CAPMT-Contemporary Piano competitions in the past and the second place at the American Protégé International Music Talent Competition and performed at the Carnegie Hall, New York in Spring 2019 and Summer 2022. In 2020, I won the online competition organized by Elevato, Salzburg-Austria and 2nd place in the U.S. New Star Étude competition. In 2022, I also won the Global Genius Gold Prize. In addition to piano, I also play marimba, and won the bronze prize in Marimba solo for NLPA and Grand prize for chamber group in NLPA 2022, and had a winners’ concert in Carnegie hall in April 2022. Other than spending most of his time playing music, I love to play soccer and basketball. I am also a Boy Scout and like to participate in church AWANA activities.

Born in China, Alicia started learning piano at the age of 7. After three years of learning piano, she has awarded the highest piano examination of the Central Conservatory of Music School of Piano Grading Test level 10 certificate. She then pursues her piano study in Australia. In 2014, she has accepted into the Young Conservatorium of Music, Griffith University at the age of 13. Soon she started competing in piano competitions from the age of 15, participating and winning multiple prizes in the Queensland Piano Competition from 2016 to 2019, Brisbane Youth International Music Festival, Sydney Eisteddfod. Between the year of 2019 and 2020, she has been awarded AMusA and LMusA certificates both for piano respectively. Alicia has given numerous recitals in China and Australia and performed in many masterclasses. She has studied piano with Russian tutelages Oleg Stepanov, Natasha Vlasenko and Igor Machlak and Australian pianist Glenn Riddle. She is also the recipient in major scholarships during her studies at university. Alicia is now studying her third year at Sydney Conservatorium of Music with Head of Keyboard Professor Stephanie McCallum.

Ramona Munteanu was born in Cluj Napoca, Romania. She began studying piano at the age of 5. She graduated the Sigismund Toduta Music Lyceum in 2000. In 2005 she received a diploma in piano performance at the Gheoghe Dima Academy of Music in Cluj Napoca. She then continued her studies, attending courses for a Master’s degree at the same Academy and received a post-graduate degree in piano with the maximum grades. In 2010 she obtained a second post-graduate degree at the Benedetto Marcello Conservatory in Venice. Ramona Munteanu began her concert activity very early, appearing as soloist at the age of nine with the Symphonic Orchestra of the Music Lyceum in Cluj Napoca, Romania. She has won national and international musical competitions: 2009 third prize at the national competition “Citta di Piove di Sacco,” Italy in the chamber music section. In the same year, she won the competition to perform with the orchestra of the “Teatro La Fenice”. In April 2011 she won Third Prize in two categories, soloist and chamber music, in the national competition “Citta di Piove di Sacco”. In July 2011 she won Second Prize at the international competition “Festival di Bellagio and Lake Como” in the chamber music category. In 2018, she won the First Prize in the international competition “Note sul mare” in Rome. In 2021 she won a special mention at the International Competition as a professional pianists “Medici International Piano Competition”.In the past few years she has been actively involved in concert activity as a soloist and in chamber groups, performing in prestigious venues such as the Teatro la Fenice, Teatro Malibran, Teatro Goldoni, Palazzo Labia, Ateneo Veneto, Palazzo Liviano Padua, Teatro di Marcello Rome ecc. She participated at various Music Festivals in Italy : Festival Delle Nazioni - Teatro di Marcello ( Roma), Il Suono di Vino, Sogliano al Rubicone (Rimini) , Zungoli Classica ( Benevento), Hands on piano (Aveiro, Portugal), Mallorca Summer Academy (Palma de Mallorca, Spagna), Autunno musicale (Cosenza, Italy), Piano City Milano, Piano City Pordenone ecc.

Born on 2012 in Bangkok, Thailand, Chanya Bayla Somboonvechakarn is Thai-Indonesian who has been under tutelage of Prof. Irina Novikova since 2016. At the age of 6 years old, Bayla made her first debut as Concert Soloist with Sunrise String Orchestra at Chulalongkorn University Music Hall, performing Berkovich Concerto Op. 44 No. On December 2019, Bayla had the opportunity to perform as Guest Pianist at The International Philharmonic Children of Future Concerts in Moscow; organized by Children Philharmonic Society and partnered by NEWSMUZ.com, Russia News and ORPHEUS9.2FM, with the presence of the Thai Ambassador. Bayla enjoys traveling and has won many prizes from various music competitions/festivals. She has performed in many gala concerts in music halls around the world, such as Moscow, Osaka and Hamamatsu, Hongkong, Rome, Budapest, New York, Singapore and Bangkok. Bayla passed her ABRSM Grade 8 Piano examination with Distinction on her 9th birthday. Bayla’s passion for music expands beyond the piano, to strings and vocal. Bayla is an active member of string orchestra in her school and enjoys sharing her passion for music with others. On top of her music achievements, Bayla is also a capable young mathematician and takes a curious interest in English literature. She is a member of MENSA International, the High IQ Society. Her passion for music, arts and literature bolsters her aspiration to be a well-rounded individual with deep theoretical and practical skills in the areas of her expertise.

Emily Tan Yi Rui, 9, started learning Piano and Violin at a very tender age of 4. Additionally, she picked up Guzheng during the Covid-19 lockdown in Singapore and score Distinction for Grade 3 practical exams. She has since then continued this as her 3rd music instrument. She has also won several international and national awards last year including 3 1st prizes in all 3 instruments categories for IMKA Music competition. She was awarded 1st place at Red Maple Keyboard competition, Young Musicians Category and was invited to perform in Toronto, Canada when the concert halls reopen. She was awarded Champion for Grade 1 & 2 Piano in the 3rd ASCO International Music Competition. She has topped the charts for Performance Grade 2 (Gold Prize for Piano), clinching the title of All Round Musician Award for winning 2 or more prizes under different instruments. She was also awarded LYM Annual Star Awards. She was also invited to be in the list of Season 2023 Recitals at Carnegie Hall. She plays Christmas songs on her violin during Christmas visits to the old folks’ home yearly. Often, she was tasked to perform during school concerts and recitals. She hopes that her music passion will continue to bring smiles and love to everyone in the world.

I am Rashana and I am 12 years old. I live in Singapore. I started learning the piano at the age of 6 under my teacher, Ms Kee Kannie. I won the Platinum Award for the 6th Singapore Performers' Festival and Chamber Music Competition when I was 7. At age 10, I was the Platinum award winner in the 1st Le Petit Performers' Fest. At age 12, I took part in the ARS Nova International Music Competition and received the Gold award. Also at age 12, I came in 1st in my category at the Joyeux Music International competition. Besides competitions, I scored straight Distinctions in all my graded ABRSM piano exams. I am in the Music Elective Programme in my school and my co-curricular activity is band, where I am learning to play the clarinet. Besides playing the piano, I enjoy reading, baking, swimming and spending time with my family.

Hello, my name is Jonathan, I am 15 years old and I am from Germany. I started playing the piano at the age of 4 and have been taught by Romuald Noll at the Musikschule Stuttgart since 2015. Since my first competition at the age of six, I have successfully participated in numerous competitions, both for solo piano and chamber music, such as 1st prizes at the Tonkünstlerwettbewerb, several prizes at the Münchner Klavierpodium and a 3rd prize at the Köthener Bachwettbewerb. I have also won several 1st prizes at Jugend Musiziert. Through the support of the Stuttgart Music School I was allowed to participate in larger concerts, during the Corona Pandemic also in several livestreams. Besides the piano I also play the cello intensively, also here I could achieve many competition successes.

Maddox Marsollek (born December 2013) began taking piano lessons at the age of three. After only ten months of lessons, Maddox made his debut at a summer concert in the Castle church Altlandsberg and has so far played more than 35 concerts. Maddox is taught by concert pianist and Echo Prize winner Elisaveta Blumina. In August 2019 she invited him as the youngest up-and-coming musician to an international master class in Israel, where he also played in the final concert in Elma Hall. Since August 2019 Maddox has also received composition lessons. In the same month he composed his first piece. In the meantime he has composed more than 10 works, most recently a sonatina in 3 movements (for violin and piano) and a two-part invention. Currently working on a quartet for violin, viola, cello and piano. In 2020 and 2021 he has so far won a total of 58 international awards (mainly as a soloist, but also in a duo with his brother Miles, violin, 6 years old) at competitions in Germany, Poland, Russia, Latvia, Ukraine, Estonia, Italy, Spain, France, Greece, Switzerland, Great Britain, Scandinavia, Bosnia-Herzegovina, Indonesia, Japan, China, Canada and the USA won, some in age groups up to 12 years. He always won 1st (a total of 24 and one absolute price) to 3rd prizes as well as various special prizes for an “Exceptional Young Talent” and the best interpretation of contemporary compositions. There are also four first prizes in national competitions. After Maddox had given concerts in the Emperor Hall in Füssen, the Beethoven House in Bonn and the Solitär Mozarteum in Salzburg in the summer of 2021, he appeared in a young talent concert at the Berlin State Opera at the end of September, in which two of his compositions (an arrangement for voice, violin and piano as well as a sonatina in 3 movements for violin and piano) were premiered. In December 2021 Maddox he made his debut at the Teatro Studio, Parco della Musica in Rome.

My name is Lee,Lien-Jie. I am six years old. I am from Tamsui, Taiwan. I began to play piano at the age of four ; with prof. Karen Chiang. Prof.Chiang, made me fall in love with music and playing the piano. She instilled within me, that piano is more than just playing the correct keys and notes. Instead, you need to immerse your entire body into the experience. Listen intently with your ears, visualize the music, flow with the rhythm but most important play from the heart. Her guidance and patience, has allowed me to consistently improve and push the boundaries of my playing. To continue improving and to be the best I can be; I practice each day at home. I dedicate two hours everyday to perfect my skill. My hope is , my hard work and love of piano is always showcased within my performances, so my music can touch everyone’s hearts.

My name is Isabella Xue, currently 10 years old. I have been Peyhwan Kuan’s student since May 2018. I am one of the Grand Prix winners in the 2021 International Piano Competition Paderewski in Memoriam and the Platinum Medal in 2021 Quebec Music Competition. I won the Absolute First Prize in the 4th International Competition of Musical Execution "City of Sarzana”. In the 2021 Medici International Music Competition I won the First Prize. At the 2021 Great Masters International Piano Competition and the 1st Swiss International Online Competition I won First Place. I also won the 2021 Pacific Music Society and Foundation Scholarships in the first age category Piano competition. At the 2nd WPTA Singapore International Piano Competition, I won Platinum Award and Best Romantic Award. I am the 1st place winner in the 2020 Putra International Piano Competition and the Neapolitan Masters Competition, the first place winner and Beethoven Prize of the 2020 Virtual International Music Competition organized by the Chopin Society Malaysia. Besides winning 1st, I was also named TOP PERFORMER RUNNER UP PRIZE at 2020 US New Star Music Competition by Composer Chopin & Bach. I won the 1st Prize in the 2020 COSTA RICA Piano Festival Online Competition.

I am Xingchen Lin. I was born on November 6, 2009. I started studying in 2018 and have been studying for 3 years. Under the guidance of pianist Shan Jiang. I have taken ABRSM grade 5 piano performance and passed with distinction in 2021. I won first prize in King’s Peak International Music Competition 2021. I won first place in the Socal International Piano Competition in 2021. Also, I won first place in the MAP International Music Competition in 2021. I also won 1 Gold Prizes and 2 Silver prizes in the Global Genius Competition this year. I like piano because it is expressive in ways that cannot be done with words or expressions. I am very happy to be able to participate in this competition. Classical music makes me excited and I really enjoy the stage very much.

Benjamin Slive discovered early the power of music to bring people together. Benjamin began his piano studies at the age of 5, and has been studying with Tiffany Goff for the past four years. An enthusiastic lover of music, Benjamin embraces every chance to share his art with others. He has participated in numerous studio and school recitals in Florida and Ohio, and regularly shares his time and talent playing for residents of South Florida assisted living facilities. As a piano duo, Benjamin and his twin brother Julian have enjoyed performing at Carnegie Hall, NY on several occasions as 1st and 2nd prize winners of the 2018 and 2021 Florida Keys International Music Competition, and 2nd and 3rd prize winners of the 2019 and 2021 American Protégé International Music Talent Competition. They also took 2nd prize in the 2020 Florida Keys Competition, and were invited to perform at Aventura Arts & Cultural Center in Florida. Together, they participated in a masterclass with Profs. Judith Burganger and Leonid Treer, as well as taking home the gold and silver medals in the 2020 Golden Key International Music Festival. Benjamin is also an accomplished lacrosse player, and devoted to athletic endeavors including tennis and swimming. He equally enjoys his academic studies, where his favorite subjects are language arts, math, and science. He was his school’s spelling bee champion for two years—a proud accomplishment. When not pursuing one of his many activities, Benjamin loves spending time with his family, including his mom, dad, brother Julian, tiny dog Phoebe, and big puppy Everest

Julian Slive began his piano studies at age 5, and has been studying with Tiffany Goff for four years. Passionate about music, Julian especially enjoys the privilege of performing for others, and bringing joy to his listeners. He has participated in numerous studio and school recitals in Florida and Ohio, and regularly shares his time and talent playing for residents of South Florida assisted living facilities. Julian has taken home multiple prizes, including 2nd prize in the 2020 Florida Keys International Music Talent Competition, and honors in the 2021 Palm Beach County MTA Judged Musicale. As a piano duo, Julian and his twin brother Benjamin have enjoyed performing at Carnegie Hall, NY on several occasions as 1st and 2nd prize winners of the 2018 and 2021 Florida Keys International Music Competition, and 2nd and 3rd prize winners of the 2019 and 2021 American Protégé International Music Talent Competition. They also took 2nd prize in the 2020 Florida Keys Competition, and were invited to perform at Aventura Arts & Cultural Center in Florida. Together, they participated in a masterclass with Profs. Judith Burganger and Leonid Treer, as well as taking home the gold and silver medals in the 2020 Golden Key International Music Festival. Julian is also an accomplished lacrosse player, representing his travel lacrosse team as the face off midfielder. He also enjoys other athletic activities, including tennis and competing in junior ski slalom races. Equally devoted to academics, Julian's favorite subjects are math and science. In his spare time, Julian likes to create art, listen to music, cook, and enjoy the company of friends in his home, where he loves spending time with his mom, dad, brother Ben, tiny dog Phoebe, and big puppy Everest.

Hi my name is Justin Liaw, I am 12 years old. I began my musical training in 2015 at U Music Education Foundation learning to play various percussion instruments. In the subsequent years from 2016-2019, I performed with the Percussion Chamber group at the annual concert organized by U Music. I focused more seriously on learning to play the piano in March 2020 with Ms. Peyhwan Kuan when all chamber classes and live concerts were cancelled. In 2020, I won third place at American Protégée International Competition and will be playing at Carnegie Hall (date is unknown due to the pandemic). I am also thrilled that I was able to compete at the 2021 Piano Star Virtual Competition and won third place. Besides music, I participated in many local, regional and national badminton tournaments. During the pandemic, I continue to attend Taekwondo classes at Mach Martial Arts and received first-dan black belt. I am looking forward to being able to perform in live concerts soon, so I can share music with audiences.

My name is Frederick Chiu. I am 16 years old. I was born in the United States to a Taiwanese family. I began my piano education at the age of five under the guidance of my father. I started to participate in piano competitions when I was ten, and I won numerous awards in local and international competitions. In December 2020, I have been selected as a First Prize and Exceptional Young Talent Special Prize winner in the International Music Competition Bonn "Grand Prize Virtuoso" in German. I was invited to perform at Carnegie Hall, New York, as a first prize winner of the 2017 Golden Classical Music Awards International Competition. In additional to competition, I have also successfully passed the Music Teacher Association of California (MTAC) Certificate of Merit Advanced Level with honor and also selected to participate in the Panel Finals in 2021. Besides piano, I have developed an interest in Forensic Sciences and Medical Pathology. I wish to continue this interest and pursue both Science and Music majors later in college.

I have been playing the piano since I was five years old. At the age of six I won a first prize in a music competition for the first time. Since then I have successfully participated in numerous competitions, both piano solo and chamber music. I won the first prize at the International Euregio Piano Competition in Geilenkirchen, the first prize at the International Piano Competition Young Piano Stars in Königs Wusterhausen and was a finalist in the International Piano Competition in Brussels. Together with my brother I was a prizewinner at the national competition jugend musiziert. My piano teacher is the pianist Romuald Noll at the Stuttgart Music School. In the music school I am in the promotion of gifted students.I was allowed to give many concerts in big concert halls. Because of the corona pandemic, many concerts were offered as streaming concerts Because of the corona pandemic, many concerts were offered as streaming concerts. I am now submitting such a livestream as a competition entry. With kind regards Vitus Polley

Helena Królówna was born and lives in Gdańsk in Poland. She is a student of Zygmunt Noskowski Music School (2nd level of education) in Gdynia. Helena studies on two specialities: vocalism and instrumental studies (piano). From the very beginning of her musical education, Helena has exhibited her distinctive sense of music, which allowed her to take part in many piano, chamber music and vocal competitions, both regional, national and international. She is a laureate of over 40 competitions. Helena as a pianist focuses on interpretating works of Beethoven and Chopin mainly as these composers’ music is the closest to her heart and evoke the strongest emotions. Her special musical intuition makes her performances unconventional, but she always emphasises it is not her aim in itself to be original or controversial. Helena also plans to become an orchestra conductor to fully express herself and share her vision of music with the world.

James Matthews 32, a native of Lakeland, Florida is a Professor of Piano at Belmont University in Nashville Tennessee. James received his Masters Degree from Belmont University and his Bachelor’s Degree from the University of West Florida. After spending his first year of college being homeless. Matthews has gone above and beyond his personal struggles and has achieved numerous prizes in piano competitions that lead to a Medal of Musical Excellence from the City of New York, after his first Carnegie Hall debut in April of 2014 James has been featured on The Ellen DeGeneres Show, People Magazine, Good Morning America, NPR and BBC World News and has performed solo in all of the United States in North America being known for his dramatic romantic piano music performances. In 2015 Matthews returned to Carnegie Hall for an encore performance with the music of Franz Liszt. The New York Post quotes James as being a “Rising Star” James continues to be inspirational to many with his faith based determination and love for music.

Hello! My name is Radik. I am 21 years old. I am from Russia, the city of Nizhny Novgorod. He graduated from the first year of the Nizhny Novgorod Conservatory named after Glinka. Before that, I studied at the music college of the city of Izhevsk. During my first year at the conservatory, I studied a lot of repertoire: "Partita No. 3" by J. S. Bach," The first part of Concerto No. 2 for Piano and Orchestra "by D. Shostakovich, "Ballad No. 2" by F. Liszt," Interlude and Fugue in E "by P. Hindemith," Kreislerian "by R. Schumann, more Tchaikovsky pieces:" Nocturne"," In the manner of Chopin "and" Toccata " by K. Cherni. I hope that I will be able to pass even more new works by different composers and show myself in competitions of a" serious " level. I wish all the participants of the contest only good luck and hard work!!!

Weronika Bujok - third-year student in the piano class of Professor Milena Kędra at the Krzysztof Penderecki Academy of Music in Krakow. Weronika was born in 1999 and began learning to play the piano at the age of 6. Her solo achievements include: Fourth Prize at the 11th International Competition of Musical Interpretation in Przemyśl, Poland in 2017; Distinction on the II. Danubia Talents Liszt International Piano Competition in Rome in 2019. in September 2018 and 2019 she performed solo and in a chamber ensemble during two editions of the International Chamber Music Festival "Music On The Heights" in Zakopane. Weronika, apart from playing solo, has been a member of the chamber ensemble 'duoBujok' since 2018, in which she plays with her violinist sister. In a duo she won the following prizes in competitions: the First Prize at the II Wiener Danubia Talents International Music Competition (Vienna, Austria, 26.02.2020) and Second Prize at the 1st ISCART International Online Music Competition (Lugano, Switzerland, 18.09.2020), Honourable Mention at the XX International Juliusz Zarebski Music Competition (Poland, Warsaw, 15.12.2020), Third Prize at the 3rd AEMC (Associazione Europea di Musica e Comunicazione) International Chamber Music Competition (Montacassiano, Italy, 8.03.2021), Second Prize at the King’s Peak International Music Competition (USA, 6.04.2021), Distinction Award at the 1st International Chamber Music Competition „KraCamera” 2021 (29-31.05.2021, Cracow, Poland). In 2020, Weronika received a scholarship from the Rector of the Academy of Music in Krakow for her achievements. Weronika Bujok takes part in numerous master classes under the supervision of outstanding professors, such as: Andrzej Jasiński, Evgeny Sinaiski, Maria Szwajger - Kułakowska, Beata Bilińska and others.

Sophia Lu (LU SHU FEI)

Sophia was born on Sept. 19th 2000 in Pingtung city, Taiwan.

Since early childhood, Sophia has always possessed a natural talent for music. She is a considerate and appreciative young person that has embraced all of the benefits and challenges of the Classical music world.

She is competent on the following instruments: Piano, Violin, Cello, Clarinet, Guitar, Marimba, and Percussion.

Having grown up in a very musical family, she has been performing for various public and private functions since an early age. This has included: Singing, Dancing, Theater, Benefit Concerts, and Studio Recordings. Through her hard work and disciplined approach, she has won many distinguished prizes and awards in various competitions.

She recorded a Jingle for Taiwan’s second largest City, Kaohsiung, for the Police commercial radio station, for which she was nominated at the annual Golden Bell Awards. She also sang on an album that was nominated for a Golden Melody Award. This album was produced by her mother Ms. Shirley Jen who is herself a very well known concert pianist and arranger/songwriter.

Sophia’s classmates have nicknamed her “Master of instruments”. She is currently studying at Musik Hochschule Köln, majoring in Piano performance .

She is now receiving teaching under Prof. Sheila Arnold.

Her former music instructors are listed below:

Nicolò Giuliano Tuccia began studying the piano at a very young age under the guidance of maestro Giancarlo Peroni.

Subsequently he graduated under the guidance of Prof. Manila Santini at the "Liceo Musicale Statale Canova" in Forlì.

In the same year, under the guidance of Maestro Paolo Wolfango Cremonte, he obtained the three-year academic title with full marks and honors at the "G.Lettimi" Musical Institute in Rimini.

He currently attends courses with the masters Pietro de Maria, Andrea Lucchesini and Enrico Stellini at the Pinerolo Music Academy.

He also attends the two-year piano academic year with Maestro Massimiliano Ferrati at the “A.Steffani” Conservatory in Castelfranco Veneto.

During his musical career, Nicolò Giuliano Tuccia perfected himself with various masters and held national and international master classes.

The masters with whom he had the pleasure of improving are: Mauro Minguzzi, Alessandra Ammara, Luigi Tanganelli, Riccardo Risaliti, Emanuel Krasovsky, Sergio Tiempo, Massimiliano Ferrati, Roberto Cappello, Edith Fischer, Siavush Gadjev, Antonio Pomp-Baldi, Pablo Galdo, Andrea Lucchesini.

Nicolò Giuliano Tuccia was also the winner of national and international awards, always placing himself in the very first places.

The competitions where he distinguished himself positively are: "Alberghini Prize" of Castel Maggiore, 1st absolute prize, "Zangarelli Prize" 1st prize, "Città del Borgo dell’angelo" Competition 1st absolute prize,

"City of Riccione" 2nd prize, "City of Magliano Sabina" 2nd prize, "Humberto Quagliata Prize" 2nd prize, recently also obtained an "honorable mention" in the "Sergio Fiorentino" Online Piano competition.

Born in Komotini, Greece. He attended preliminary music classes at the age of six and then piano courses in the Conservatory of Contemporary Music of Eleni Xygala as well as courses in music theory. In July 2005 he received his Degree in Harmony with Distinction and in June 2007 the Diploma of Piano Performance with Distinction and 1st Prize. In 2007 he received an Honorary award from the Greek Mathematical Association. From 2006 to 2014 he studied Applied Physics in the School of Applied Mathematics and Natural Sciences at the National Technical University of Athens (N.T.U.A.). As an undergraduate student he participated in the International School of Plasma Physics and Technology organized by the University of Thessaly , Volos in 2009. He completed and defended his Diploma Thesis on Phase Coexistence in Double-Band Quantum Order Parameters in FeSn in September 2014. This work was a part of a collaboration between Cavendish Laboratory, Cambridge University and many other Institutes around Europe working on Solid State Physics and resulted in a joint thesis publication afterwards. As a piano student since 1998, he participated in the annual concerts of the Conservatoire until 2006. Since January 2008 he is a member of the Mixed Choir of the N.T.U.A.. He has also attended orchestral and choral conducting seminars and masterclasses in Athens and has conducted the City of Athens Music Ensembles. He has participated in many concerts in Athens and Qatar as an accompanist/member on the piano as well as individual vocal soloists - including members of the National Opera House in numerous artistic events and concerts. He has also given piano recitals and collaborated with ensembles in Athens, Greece. He was awarded a scholarship to study Piano Performance at the Keyboard Department of the Royal Birmingham Conservatoire with Daniel Browell and Dr. Robert Markham. He graduated as MMus with Distinction and two prizes He has participated in numerous competitions and masterclasses taken by George Martin, Peter Donohoe, Albert Tiu and John Leneham. He frequently collaborates with the Vocal and String Departments and has appeared in numerous concerts and festivals. He has performed in the presence of the Nigerian King, His Imperial Majesty, Ooni of Ile-Ife and has recently appeared in France 3 TV Network. He is finalist in many song and chamber music competitions (Town Hall, Herbert Lumpy, Stuart Cameron)as pianist-accompanist and was a finalist at the Peter Donohoe Prize for soloists. He won second prize at the Birmingham Philharmonic Orchestra Concerto Competition playing the Arensky Piano Concerto and appeared in Lichfield international Music Festival. He has also composed two piano concertos, several piano miniatures and a symphonic poem. He is now working on a lyrical adaptation based on the work of J.R.R. Tolkien. He is currently a member of staff at Berkshire Young Musicians Trust, Ltd. where he frequently appears as a performer in numerous events.

Jack Tyndale-Biscoe’s unorthodox musical background spans three continents, two instruments and encompasses performances from Bach to Britten. After many years as an autodidact, his international studies have included Performance Diploma's {P.DipIMEB) from the Australian International Conservatorium of Music, Bachelor's degree in Piano Performance from Brigham Young University-Idaho and a Postgraduate Performance degree from the Royal College of Music in London. In aim to pursue added training, in 2017 and 2018 he attended the Rebecca Penney’s Piano Festival in Tampa, Florida. There he participated in lessons and master classes with world-renowned teachers from Juilliard, Eastman, Indiana University, as well as many other prestigious musical institutions in the United States. Jack T-B owes much to the intense musical instruction received in Florida, which has included prizewinners of the Van Cliburn, Gina Bachauer, William Kapell, Cleveland International and Paloma O’Shea Santander competitions. He has performed on numerous occasions at concert halls and venues primarily in Europe, the Unites States and Australia. Highlights have included playing in Málaga, Madrid, and Barcelona, presenting Spanish solo piano repertoire, placing particular emphasis on Albéniz, Granados and Mompou. Recent Live performances include: St. James Church (Holland Park), Exhibition Road, Knightsbridge, the Royal College of Music East Parry Room, the Amaryllis Flemming Concert Hall as well as the Performance Hall at the Royal College of Music, St. Barnabas Church (Kensington), Lecture-Recital on Albéniz in the Recital Hall at BYU-I, and WUSF Radio 89.7 FM, Classical Radio. Since 2021, Jack Tyndale-Biscoe is a Talented Unlimited UK artist.

Peng Jin is a professional pianist from China. During that time, he won the first prize of 17-19 years old adolescent group China division in ninth Chopin International Piano Competition (Golden Ring). He subsequently won the first prize of advanced Chinese music works in the No. 18 Hong Kong-Asia Open Competition. In 2015, he won the second prize in the 7th U.S. United Young Musician International Piano Competition, and he joined the member of American Beacon Artists Association. In 2017, he has also won the third prize in the Asian Music Competition, and won the first prize of piano in No. 8 Asia Pacific International Arts Festival, and won the title of Art Nova. As a performer, he regularly performs solo recitals, chamber concerts and teacher-student concerts, also he has experience volunteering to perform in the Elder House. In 2018-2019, he has performed many times in the Perugia Music Festival in Italy, studied under Professor Jeromel Lowenthal of the Juilliard School, and Professor Markus Groh of Berlin University of the Arts. He earned a Bachelor of Music Degree from the Tianjin Conservatory of Music, from 2013 through 2017. He also earned a Master Music Degree in Piano Performance at Boston Conservatory at Berklee in 2020. Mr. Jin is currently studying for a University of Minnesota Doctor of Musical Arts program, studying under Professor Paul Shaw. And he is also studying the harpsichord performance for his secondary major, studying under Professor Dean Billmeyer.

Daniel Pérez has provided his knowledge as an educator in various institutions of Panama City. As an orchestral musician, he has performed with various groups in the country, including the National Symphony Orchestra of Panama. He has participated in internationally renowned events in which we can highlight The Orchestra of the America, also has first place in the World Music Competition (Serbia), recognition of the Southern Percussion International Tuned Competition (United Kingdom) and honorable mention in the Young Soloist Contest of the XII Alfredo De Saint Malo International Music Festival (Panama). During his training as a musician, he has received classes with renowned international teachers. Daniel has obtain Graduate Artists Certificate in Orchestral Performance with OAcademy. He is currently finishing his bachelor's degree in music with an emphasis in percussion from the University of Panama, where he studies under the tutelage of Dr. Carlos Camacho.
